39int
40gf119_disp_root_scanoutpos(NV50_DISP_MTHD_V0)
41{
42 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
43 const u32 total = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x640414 + (head * 0x300));
44 const u32 blanke = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x64041c + (head * 0x300));
45 const u32 blanks = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x640420 + (head * 0x300));
46 union {
47 struct nv04_disp_scanoutpos_v0 v0;
48 } *args = data;
49 int ret;
50
51 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp scanoutpos size %d\n", size);
52 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
53 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp scanoutpos vers %d\n",
54 args->v0.version);
55 args->v0.vblanke = (blanke & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
56 args->v0.hblanke = (blanke & 0x0000ffff);
57 args->v0.vblanks = (blanks & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
58 args->v0.hblanks = (blanks & 0x0000ffff);
59 args->v0.vtotal = ( total & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
60 args->v0.htotal = ( total & 0x0000ffff);
61 args->v0.time[0] = ktime_to_ns(ktime_get());
62 args->v0.vline = /* vline read locks hline */
63 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616340 + (head * 0x800)) & 0xffff;
64 args->v0.time[1] = ktime_to_ns(ktime_get());
65 args->v0.hline =
66 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616344 + (head * 0x800)) & 0xffff;
67 } else
68 return ret;
69
70 return 0;
71}
72
73void
74gf119_disp_root_fini(struct nv50_disp_root *root)
75{
76 struct nvkm_device *device = root->disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
77 /* disable all interrupts */
78 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6100b0, 0x00000000);
79}
80
81int
82gf119_disp_root_init(struct nv50_disp_root *root)
83{
84 struct nv50_disp *disp = root->disp;
85 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
86 u32 tmp;
87 int i;
88
89 /* The below segments of code copying values from one register to
90 * another appear to inform EVO of the display capabilities or
91 * something similar.
92 */
93
94 /* ... CRTC caps */
95 for (i = 0; i < disp->base.head.nr; i++) {
96 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616104 + (i * 0x800));
97 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101b4 + (i * 0x800), tmp);
98 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616108 + (i * 0x800));
99 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101b8 + (i * 0x800), tmp);
100 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61610c + (i * 0x800));
101 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101bc + (i * 0x800), tmp);
102 }
103
104 /* ... DAC caps */
105 for (i = 0; i < disp->func->dac.nr; i++) {
106 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61a000 + (i * 0x800));
107 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101c0 + (i * 0x800), tmp);
108 }
109
110 /* ... SOR caps */
111 for (i = 0; i < disp->func->sor.nr; i++) {
112 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c000 + (i * 0x800));
113 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6301c4 + (i * 0x800), tmp);
114 }
115
116 /* steal display away from vbios, or something like that */
117 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6100ac) & 0x00000100) {
118 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6100ac, 0x00000100);
119 nvkm_mask(device, 0x6194e8, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
120 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
121 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6194e8) & 0x00000002))
122 break;
123 ) < 0)
124 return -EBUSY;
125 }
126
127 /* point at display engine memory area (hash table, objects) */
128 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610010, (root->instmem->addr >> 8) | 9);
129
130 /* enable supervisor interrupts, disable everything else */
131 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610090, 0x00000000);
132 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6100a0, 0x00000000);
133 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6100b0, 0x00000307);
134
135 /* disable underflow reporting, preventing an intermittent issue
136 * on some gk104 boards where the production vbios left this
137 * setting enabled by default.
138 *
139 * ftp://download.nvidia.com/open-gpu-doc/gk104-disable-underflow-reporting/1/gk104-disable-underflow-reporting.txt
140 */
141 for (i = 0; i < disp->base.head.nr; i++)
142 nvkm_mask(device, 0x616308 + (i * 0x800), 0x00000111, 0x00000010);
143
144 return 0;
145}

147static const struct nv50_disp_root_func
148gf119_disp_root = {
149 .init = gf119_disp_root_init,
150 .fini = gf119_disp_root_fini,
151 .dmac = {
152 &gf119_disp_core_oclass,
153 &gf119_disp_base_oclass,
154 &gf119_disp_ovly_oclass,
155 },
156 .pioc = {
157 &gf119_disp_oimm_oclass,
158 &gf119_disp_curs_oclass,
159 },
160};
161
162static int
163gf119_disp_root_new(struct nvkm_disp *disp, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
164 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
165{
166 return nv50_disp_root_new_(&gf119_disp_root, disp, oclass,
167 data, size, pobject);
168}

170const struct nvkm_disp_oclass
171gf119_disp_root_oclass = {
172 .base.oclass = GF110_DISP,
173 .base.minver = -1,
174 .base.maxver = -1,
175 .ctor = gf119_disp_root_new,
176};
